Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at an event in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, where she praised the workers and labor unions for their contributions to the country. She highlighted the importance of investing in workers and announced updates to the Davis-Bacon Act, which will result in higher wages for workers on federally funded construction projects. Harris emphasized that fair wages are essential and that the Biden administration is committed to building an economy that supports working families. She also mentioned the positive impact of Bidenomics, citing low unemployment rates, rising wages, and falling inflation. Harris concluded by expressing her belief in the dignity of all work and the need to create an economy that allows all people to thrive.